            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 8,
            "weighted_score": 0.6241886019706726,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Coming back to this game after playing LMU made me realize just how good ACC is.\r\n\r\nThe sound design is off the charts.  Going from LMU to ACC driving the same GT3 Lexus RC F... it sounded SO MUCH BETTER in ACC.  Online racing is way easier to get into, and faster.  Faster loading, less bugs, great driving model and physics.  This game is the ultimate GT racing sim and I love it.  \r\n\r\nOnly big downside is that VR support is dogwater.  The visuals are very blurry even at upscaled resolutions on a Quest 3, and fps takes a nice hit.  You can tweak the VR settings to make it look much better, but it involves going into .ini files and making tweaks there as well as in game and in your VR software.  Shouldn't be that way, the VR support should be as seamless and easy on the eyes as the original Assetto Corsa, which has fantastic VR support."
        },
