        {
            "review_id": "227245211",
            "steam_id": "76561199223783262",
            "playtime_minutes": 67,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "For all I know, the Asetto game genre has been pretty terrible. Asseto Corsa had terrible graphics, Asetto Corsa Evo was just buggy and laggy, but Asetto Corza Competizione, this one is actually playable. if you get any game from the Asetto series, get this one. It's hard to learn, but fun in the end. There's lots of tracks, and just the right amount of DLC.The graphics are next-gen, and each car is unique. I highly recommend this game to any car lover. it's great on Xbox 360 controllers, but don't do keyboard. very good game, and the only good game in the Asetto genre."
        },
