        {
            "review_id": "225985928",
            "steam_id": "76561198119141351",
            "playtime_minutes": 37903,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "At first, I couldn’t get used to the braking behavior, so I tried other simulators and let ACC gather dust for years. Last week, I picked it up again and tested GT4 and the BMW M2 CS in single-player races against the AI, and I was actually surprised. Braking with the right pedal settings works great and still feels natural; even the AI is very reliable, and I’m having great races. This simulator takes some getting used to but feels lively; the graphics are beautiful and the car sounds are great to, I highly recommend it, though you’ll need to put some time into it.\n\n"
        },
