        {
            "review_id": "225848778",
            "steam_id": "76561198443367663",
            "playtime_minutes": 6023,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 1,
            "weighted_score": 0.523809552192688,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "My love for racing started with NFS Most Wanted 2005, finished it six times, spent way too long trying to beat Razor before realizing the tire puncture was just part of the game. Went through Underground, Hot Pursuit, Most Wanted 2012 after that. Got my first Thrustmaster Ferrari wheel at 12 with money I made from \r\n programs, jumped into Euro Truck and Forza Horizon 3, then spent the next six or seven years deep in competitive FPS, CS, Valorant, eventually CS2.\r\nAt 22 I bought a PXN V99. Euro Truck and Forza 4 were fine, but something was missing. I'd been watching F1 since 2019, every race, every quali, every practice session, so when I found LMP and GT3 racing it made sense to go looking for something more serious. That's how I landed on ACC.\r\nFirst few hours were rough. Bought the Nürburgring 24H DLC to practice and couldn't finish a single lap. Started watching esport drivers do the circuit, found an aggressive BMW M4 setup I still use everywhere, and slowly started actually learning, trail braking, slip angles, throwing the car instead of nursing it through corners.\r\nHit a plateau, so I pushed harder. Compressed the brake zones, trimmed the traction margins. Nothing else gives me the same feeling this game does.\r\nIf you're buying it, just get past the first 50 hours. That's when it clicks."
        },
